Ollama AI GOLD PE Bridge (v2.6.0)

The Ollama AI GOLD Bridge is an enterprise-grade transit proxy designed to connect Puppet Enterprise (PE) Infrastructure Assistant directly to Ollama Cloud (ollama.com/api/chat) on port 5001.

This bridge acts as a self-contained, high-performance middleware layer that translates OpenAI-style streaming requests from PE into Ollama’s native direct API schemas. Most importantly, it natively overcomes Puppet Enterprise's single-token registration limitations and resolves upstream parsing quirks on the Ollama Cloud platform.

🚀 Key Engineering Breakthroughs

1. Persistent Token-to-Host Caching Pipeline

Puppet Enterprise only transmits its configured Authorization token once during initial handshake registration (/validate or /v1/models) and omits it during subsequent interactive chat completions.

The Solution: The GOLD bridge captures the valid token on handshake, cleanses it, and persists it locally to disk at /opt/ollamaai/pe_hosts.txt.

Double-Key Matching: To prevent network DNS timeouts from hanging threads, the token is mapped and saved under both the resolved hostname (safeguarded by a 1.0s reverse DNS lookup timeout) and the raw source IP.

Automatic Overwrite & Protection: Re-registering from the PE console automatically overwrites existing mappings, while invalid/empty tokens are guarded against to prevent accidental erasure of active keys.

2. Upstream "Value looks like object" 400 Error Resolution

Ollama Cloud's Go-based gateway parser enforces strict unmarshaling schemas. During multi-turn chat sessions, Puppet Enterprise returns prior assistant responses containing tool calls with arguments formatted as double-escaped JSON strings (OpenAI standard).

The Solution: The bridge intercepts conversation histories and executes an aggressive Message History Sanitizer (sanitize_messages_for_ollama). It dynamically parses previous stringified tool arguments back into raw native Python dictionary objects before forwarding the payload, completely eliminating the fatal upstream error:
{"error": "Value looks like object, but can't find closing '}' symbol"}

3. Native-to-OpenAI Tool Translator

Ollama Cloud direct API accepts function schemas in a flat layout and returns tool calls in native NDJSON (Newline-Delimited JSON) streams.

The Solution: The bridge dynamically translates complex nested OpenAI tool parameters into clean, flat function schemas. During streaming, it intercepts native Ollama tool_calls chunks and translates them back to OpenAI-compatible choices delta packets so the Puppet Enterprise agent can immediately execute target infrastructure tasks (like queryPuppetDB).

