📦 Deployment & Setup

1. Installation on the Proxy Gateway

Deploy the verified stable service by running the deployment script:

sudo bash deploy_token_stable.sh


2. Configure Puppet Enterprise Console

Navigate to your Infra Assistant Settings / AI Service Configuration.

Set the AI Service URL to:

http://<YOUR_BRIDGE_IP>:5001/v1


Input your official Ollama Cloud API Key directly into the password/token field.

Run a test connection. The bridge will intercept, sanitize, and cache your token immediately.

3. Verify Live Traffic & Caching

You can watch the complete token-resolution, sanitization, and streaming pipeline execution in real time:

# Watch the explicit verbose bridge logs
tail -f /opt/ollamaai/bridge.log

# Inspect systemd stdout/stderr
journalctl -u ollamaai -f -o cat


🖥️ Management API Endpoints

The GOLD bridge exposes native REST endpoints on port 5001 for managing host-to-token connections.

1. List All Registered Puppet Enterprise Instances

Returns a complete index of cached hosts, IPs, and their associated tokens.

Request:

curl -s http://localhost:5001/api/ollamaai/hosts | json_pp


Response:

{
  "count": 2,
  "hosts": [
    {
      "host_or_ip": "neilnanocore0.c.tampuppettestenv.internal",
      "token_masked": "Bearer 3e4f9...WhItZ",
      "token_raw": "3e4f9328e71a495384072585f5413193.m2ue6YmBAlKCYZT4VDPWhItZ"
    },
    {
      "host_or_ip": "10.128.0.84",
      "token_masked": "Bearer 3e4f9...WhItZ",
      "token_raw": "3e4f9328e71a495384072585f5413193.m2ue6YmBAlKCYZT4VDPWhItZ"
    }
  ]
}


2. Delete a Host Registration

Safely removes a registration entry on disk, forcing a fresh token exchange on the next validate loop.

Delete by Hostname:

curl -X DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/ollamaai/hosts/neilnanocore0.c.tampuppettestenv.internal


Delete by IP:

curl -X DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/ollamaai/hosts/10.128.0.84


Response:

{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Host connection '10.128.0.84' deleted successfully."
}


